body:
I ran a test using the example. I was able to get it working by adding a check to the TestCaseSourceAttribute.BuildFrom method:

``` csharp
        public IEnumerable<TestMethod> BuildFrom(IMethodInfo method, Test suite)
        {
            // added:
            if (TestExecutionContext.CurrentContext != null && TestExecutionContext.CurrentContext.CurrentTest == null)
                TestExecutionContext.CurrentContext.CurrentTest = suite;

            foreach (TestCaseParameters parms in GetTestCasesFor(method))
                yield return _builder.BuildTestMethod(method, suite, parms);
        }
```

The rest of the tests ran just fine. I also ran cake with the TestAll target with no issues. I am not sure if this would impact anything else though.

From what I can see, this seems to work without modifying the API so it should be ok with backward compatibility.
